{"key":"post-9061138","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9061138</id>\n<content>I was actually going to make a similar heater for my doghouse, since we now live in an extremely cold high elevation mountain climate.&amp;nbsp; It's getting down to 10F tonight, and was 14F last night, two weeks before Halloween.&amp;nbsp; I decided to let her tough it out and grow a winter coat instead.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;One suggestion I'd make if your house is super cold.&amp;nbsp; Ground the coffee can so that if the wires short out to it, the breaker will trip.&amp;nbsp; Without a ground connection, if the hot wire shorts to the can and you touch it, you'll get knocked on your ass.&amp;nbsp; I noticed you're using two wire cords.&amp;nbsp; Get a three wire supply cord and connect the green to the coffee can for safety.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9061722</next>\n<prev>9060532</prev>\n<first>9060361</first>\n<last>9063315</last>\n<when>1223699732</when>\n<utime>10/11/08 07:35 AM</utime>\n</post>"}